      • getFlagValue

        public java.lang.String getFlagValue(java.lang.String flagNameOrAlias)
        Returns the value of the flag that matches the given name or alias.

        If allowRepeats is true for the flag, the value returned will be that of the first instance of the flag.

        If a parameter value is optional for this flag (i.e. if the { CommandLineParser.FlagDef#paramAffinity paramAffinity} of this flag is { CommandLineParser.ParamAffinity#OPTIONAL OPTIONAL}), you will not be able to use the return value to distinguish between a missing flag and a flag that is present but without a value, because null is returned in both cases. However, you can call hasFlag(String) to determine whether the flag was present or not.

        Parameters:
        flagNameOrAlias - The name of the flag to search for.
        Returns:
        The value of the flag that matches the given name, or null if no match is found.

      • getUnnamedValues

public java.util.List<java.lang.String> getUnnamedValues()

        public boolean hasFlag(java.lang.String flagNameOrAlias)
        Returns true if the specified flag was found.
